Every gesture is loaded; every stylistic nuance is grist to some commentary, a process at whose sharp end Miley Cyrus finds herself, once again.
Younger Now is the sound of Cyrus, or her record company, panicking and hitting “reset”So the mothers of small girls can rejoice: Younger Now is a twerk-free zone.
Thinkin’ is a throwback to pop R&B, while one of the album’s best songs, Bad Mood, sulks seductively.
